cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless sensor networks and localization, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The use of mobile anchors and movement strategies for localization can be related to robotics and autonomous systems.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes movement strategies for a mobile anchor to meet the requirements of a good range-free localization technique, which can be related to control systems.
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The use of mobile anchors and sensors can be related to multiagent systems, where agents interact with each other to achieve a common goal.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes path planning algorithms for a mobile anchor, which can be related to data structures and algorithms for optimization and efficiency.
